      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It feels aggressive because, in the early stages of any loan, the principal balance is at its highest, and you are paying interest on that entire large amount. Think of it like this: the interest is a small, but persistent, tax levied on the debt itself, and when the debt is huge, that tax is substantial. Your early payments are primarily covering this high initial interest cost before a significant chunk can be dedicated to the principal.",
